WEBVTT

00:00:10.370 --> 00:00:11.970
Hey… it’s okay.

00:00:12.490 --> 00:00:14.110
Don’t cry anymore.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:17.870
Can you please me just for a while?

00:00:18.960 --> 00:00:20.540
Kaeng Ranjuan curry.

00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:22.260
It smells just as good as its name.

00:00:23.150 --> 00:00:25.150
I want to marry your curry.

00:00:25.650 --> 00:00:27.590
Why would you marry a curry?

00:00:28.330 --> 00:00:31.680
I can cook it for you every day.

00:00:31.980 --> 00:00:33.050
That’s true.

00:00:34.280 --> 00:00:37.010
Then I’ll just marry the one who cooks it.

00:01:18.380 --> 00:01:19.010
Inn.

00:01:23.620 --> 00:01:24.820
Come sleep inside.

00:01:26.640 --> 00:01:27.590
It’s okay, Khun Po.

00:01:27.890 --> 00:01:29.020
I can sleep in the car.

00:01:29.770 --> 00:01:30.840
There’s plenty of space inside.

00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:32.590
Please go in.

00:01:34.759 --> 00:01:35.479
But…

00:01:35.720 --> 00:01:36.220
Inn.

00:01:40.420 --> 00:01:41.200
Alright, Khun Po.

00:01:41.390 --> 00:01:42.670
I’ll follow you in, then.

00:01:43.259 --> 00:01:44.330
That’s it.

00:02:02.100 --> 00:02:03.680
I’m actually jealous of the monk.

00:02:04.740 --> 00:02:06.150
Why would you be jealous of a monk?

00:02:06.150 --> 00:02:06.960
Well…

00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:09.259
He gets way more of your curry than I do.

00:02:09.610 --> 00:02:11.610
I only got one bowl. How is that enough for me?

00:02:16.690 --> 00:02:17.750
Hey… Inn.

00:02:17.750 --> 00:02:18.250
Yes, sir.

00:02:18.450 --> 00:02:19.550
Come make merit with me tomorrow morning.

00:02:22.630 --> 00:02:23.329
Of course, sir.

00:02:25.600 --> 00:02:26.950
Come along with us, Inn.

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:40.500
Inn.

00:02:41.300 --> 00:02:42.250
Get out. Now.

00:02:43.280 --> 00:02:44.120
Wait, Inn.

00:02:45.950 --> 00:02:46.900
Come with us.

00:02:48.030 --> 00:02:48.690
Inn.

00:02:50.810 --> 00:02:51.870
I’m sorry, Khun Po.

00:03:01.020 --> 00:03:01.990
What are you doing?

00:03:02.830 --> 00:03:03.770
And what are you doing?

00:03:04.360 --> 00:03:06.000
Why did you hit me?

00:03:07.870 --> 00:03:08.630
I just…

00:03:08.630 --> 00:03:09.540
If something’s bothering you, just say it.

00:03:13.190 --> 00:03:14.360
I’m jealous.

00:03:15.250 --> 00:03:15.770
What was that?

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:17.770
Jealous.

00:03:18.710 --> 00:03:20.000
I didn’t catch that.

00:03:20.560 --> 00:03:21.370
Jealous.

00:03:26.610 --> 00:03:27.470
Alright, alright.

00:03:28.550 --> 00:03:29.290
But…

00:03:30.380 --> 00:03:32.190
You have to apologize to me first.

00:03:37.570 --> 00:03:38.960
Sorry.

00:03:41.620 --> 00:03:43.130
Say it nicely.

00:03:43.630 --> 00:03:45.910
“I’m sorry.” Like that.

00:03:50.710 --> 00:03:52.250
I’m really sorry.

00:03:52.990 --> 00:03:54.760
I won’t do that again. I promise.

00:03:57.420 --> 00:03:58.650
Alright, alright.

00:03:58.650 --> 00:03:59.150
Let’s go.

00:03:59.350 --> 00:04:00.760
We’d better go offer alms.

00:04:01.750 --> 00:04:02.700
I’m going now.

00:04:02.700 --> 00:04:03.510
I’m going.

00:04:03.510 --> 00:04:05.170
The monks are coming…

00:04:05.860 --> 00:04:07.240
No, you can’t.

00:04:09.270 --> 00:04:10.640
Put your mask on first.

00:04:11.880 --> 00:04:13.430
Uh… it’s just that…

00:04:14.960 --> 00:04:16.050
My hands are full.

00:04:16.640 --> 00:04:17.769
Can you put it on for me?

00:04:18.860 --> 00:04:20.209
You’re good at putting other things on,

00:04:20.450 --> 00:04:21.510
But not this?

00:04:22.330 --> 00:04:23.360
You can’t manage?

00:04:26.860 --> 00:04:27.380
You…

00:04:28.890 --> 00:04:30.620
Hey, you…

00:04:30.620 --> 00:04:31.480
You.

00:04:31.480 --> 00:04:32.650
What am I supposed to do?

00:04:32.650 --> 00:04:33.940
Hey, you.

00:05:24.440 --> 00:05:28.390
May you be blessed with long life, beauty, happiness, and strength.

00:05:29.130 --> 00:05:30.380
Amen.

00:06:06.650 --> 00:06:07.790
His kiss…

00:06:09.520 --> 00:06:11.790
It completely threw me off.

00:06:18.410 --> 00:06:20.300
Why does it feel different?

00:06:22.430 --> 00:06:23.400
That “curry” kiss…

00:06:29.310 --> 00:06:31.430
And a kiss during sex…

00:06:33.159 --> 00:06:33.680
Even though…

00:06:35.060 --> 00:06:36.550
A kiss is still just a kiss.

00:06:54.430 --> 00:06:54.930
So…

00:06:55.970 --> 00:06:56.950
I’ll head off first.

00:06:58.290 --> 00:06:59.760
I should be back tomorrow afternoon.

00:07:02.130 --> 00:07:03.510
Travel safely.

00:07:06.820 --> 00:07:08.040
Hey…

00:07:12.580 --> 00:07:13.760
I…

00:07:14.450 --> 00:07:15.250
I was going to say…

00:07:16.280 --> 00:07:18.160
Don’t forget my souvenir.

00:07:21.270 --> 00:07:22.760
I thought it was something serious.

00:07:27.250 --> 00:07:30.440
Actually, I have something better than a souvenir for you today.

00:07:31.820 --> 00:07:32.990
Oh? What is it?

00:07:34.820 --> 00:07:36.350
You’ll have to wait and see.

00:08:07.210 --> 00:08:08.310
I’ll get going now.

00:08:09.100 --> 00:08:10.140
Good luck.

00:08:18.930 --> 00:08:20.170
What’s wrong with me?

00:08:20.960 --> 00:08:23.090
How did I end up like this?

00:08:24.180 --> 00:08:25.880
The more time we spend together,

00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:27.720
The more questions I have.

00:08:28.410 --> 00:08:30.420
But I don’t dare ask the ones that matter.

00:08:31.060 --> 00:08:33.440
The ones about how he really feels.

00:08:34.380 --> 00:08:35.340
Shit.

00:08:36.480 --> 00:08:38.710
Get a grip, Po. You’re losing it.

00:08:47.440 --> 00:08:48.970
Hello?

00:08:49.210 --> 00:08:50.950
Po, check your Line. Now.

00:08:52.830 --> 00:08:54.130
What the hell…

00:08:55.070 --> 00:08:56.730
He called just to say that and hung up?

00:08:57.330 --> 00:08:58.710
What’s wrong with Meen?

00:09:09.560 --> 00:09:10.610
Sasom

00:09:11.300 --> 00:09:13.110
Woraphatchalakorn

00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:15.720
Serving as a voice for the victims

00:09:17.060 --> 00:09:18.960
Arrest of alleged feng shui master Long

00:09:20.300 --> 00:09:21.660
Warning victims of impending misfortune

00:09:22.500 --> 00:09:23.180
Deceiving them into performing rituals

00:09:24.270 --> 00:09:25.960
Causing losses of over seventy million baht

00:09:29.220 --> 00:09:31.130
Shit…

00:09:33.350 --> 00:09:36.570
“Actually, I have something better than a souvenir for you today.”

00:09:36.960 --> 00:09:38.220
“Oh? What is it?”

00:09:38.520 --> 00:09:40.000
“You’ll have to wait for the surprise.”

00:09:57.250 --> 00:09:58.090
Meen.

00:09:58.490 --> 00:09:59.560
I need your help.

00:09:59.860 --> 00:10:00.550
What is it?

00:10:01.090 --> 00:10:02.720
I’m sending you a photo of my ID.

00:10:03.170 --> 00:10:04.640
Book me a flight.

00:10:04.990 --> 00:10:06.440
I’m packing.

00:10:06.440 --> 00:10:07.540
Where are you going?

00:10:07.940 --> 00:10:09.940
Singapore.

00:11:37.470 --> 00:11:40.350
Sometimes I really don’t understand…

00:11:42.620 --> 00:11:44.280
Who is he, deep down?

00:11:48.230 --> 00:11:51.080
The man who made me cry my heart out.

00:11:53.890 --> 00:11:55.140
And yet the only one

00:11:57.170 --> 00:12:00.000
Who can make me smile through tears.

00:12:04.230 --> 00:12:05.990
Today, I finally understand.

00:12:07.720 --> 00:12:10.270
He’s not just a celebrity on a magazine cover.

00:12:12.880 --> 00:12:14.960
He’s doing something significant.

00:12:16.880 --> 00:12:19.090
To protect someone.

00:12:21.510 --> 00:12:23.720
Or maybe… to protect me.

00:12:28.460 --> 00:12:30.300
But what if it’s not what I think?

00:12:35.380 --> 00:12:37.320
Am I really ready to get hurt?

00:12:41.020 --> 00:12:42.210
I don’t know.

00:12:44.530 --> 00:12:46.020
But I’ve already made my choice.

00:12:51.460 --> 00:12:53.440
I’ll find the answer on my own.

00:12:55.620 --> 00:12:56.720
I’m flying to Singapore.

00:13:15.870 --> 00:13:16.880
Falling in love

00:13:17.180 --> 00:13:19.480
Always carries a tangle of emotions,

00:13:19.480 --> 00:13:20.900
And a thrill beneath them.

00:13:22.530 --> 00:13:26.440
A peach feels like the perfect symbol of that fleeting moment,

00:13:28.220 --> 00:13:31.800
Like sweetness spilling over the instant it meets your tongue.

00:13:32.440 --> 00:13:35.440
And all those tender feelings begin to spill over,

00:13:35.440 --> 00:13:37.180
The moment we fall in love with someone.

00:13:39.050 --> 00:13:41.170
The soft, velvety skin of a peach

00:13:41.470 --> 00:13:44.200
Feels like the gentleness we ache to give.

00:13:45.680 --> 00:13:47.570
Its delicate fragrance

00:13:47.820 --> 00:13:50.550
Mirrors the quiet magic hidden within them,

00:13:51.090 --> 00:13:52.780
The part only we seem to see.

00:13:55.060 --> 00:13:57.020
And when the time comes to slice it open,

00:13:57.420 --> 00:13:59.380
To reveal the core inside,

00:14:00.220 --> 00:14:02.330
It’s no different from opening yourself up.

00:14:03.610 --> 00:14:05.600
And finally admitting

00:14:06.040 --> 00:14:08.280
That we’ve fallen for them completely.

00:14:47.020 --> 00:14:48.290
This is your room, Khun Po.

00:14:50.420 --> 00:14:51.370
Thank you.

00:15:45.680 --> 00:15:46.750
You…

00:15:49.070 --> 00:15:50.000
Po?

00:15:52.170 --> 00:15:53.280
How did you get here?

00:15:55.010 --> 00:15:56.690
Can I use the bath too?

00:16:59.030 --> 00:17:00.290
Thank you.

00:17:02.660 --> 00:17:04.750
Thank you. I really mean it.

00:17:11.460 --> 00:17:13.160
About Master Long?

00:17:18.050 --> 00:17:19.230
And…

00:17:20.609 --> 00:17:22.430
Won’t this cause you any trouble?

00:17:25.790 --> 00:17:27.280
You mean…

00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:31.130
Your parents?

00:17:36.420 --> 00:17:37.570
Don’t worry about that.

00:17:40.000 --> 00:17:41.700
As long as I get to help you,

00:17:44.070 --> 00:17:45.970
Nothing else matters.

00:17:47.200 --> 00:17:48.200
Hey.

00:17:49.680 --> 00:17:51.340
Don’t say that.

00:17:53.070 --> 00:17:55.170
You’ve already done so much for me.

00:17:57.200 --> 00:17:58.250
That’s not true.

00:18:00.570 --> 00:18:02.970
I’ve only helped you with this one thing.

00:18:05.150 --> 00:18:06.230
No…

00:18:07.510 --> 00:18:09.260
Don’t forget about the videos.

00:18:10.000 --> 00:18:12.160
That counts too.

00:18:17.740 --> 00:18:19.420
I’m really tired today.

00:18:22.480 --> 00:18:23.690
Can we…

00:18:24.680 --> 00:18:26.710
Just leave this for now?

00:18:33.570 --> 00:18:34.630
Come here…

00:18:35.620 --> 00:18:36.380
Let me give you a massage.

00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:51.520
You’re pretty good at this.

00:18:52.660 --> 00:18:53.810
Where’d you pick that up?

00:18:55.440 --> 00:18:57.330
I used to massage my grandma.

00:18:58.220 --> 00:18:59.750
I… did it for her all the time.

00:19:01.240 --> 00:19:03.690
Don’t tell me you practiced on someone else.

00:19:04.730 --> 00:19:06.080
What?

00:19:08.010 --> 00:19:10.000
Are you jealous?

00:19:55.660 --> 00:19:57.500
How have you been?

00:20:00.000 --> 00:20:01.650
I mean… work.

00:20:17.300 --> 00:20:18.010
Hey—

00:20:19.050 --> 00:20:20.000
Is that a bath bomb?

00:20:23.050 --> 00:20:24.470
A peach bath bomb?

00:20:26.400 --> 00:20:27.890
Inn knows I like it,

00:20:29.720 --> 00:20:31.020
So he bought it for me.

00:20:34.000 --> 00:20:34.990
You really…

00:20:36.970 --> 00:20:38.700
Have a thing for peaches, don’t you?

00:20:42.200 --> 00:20:42.960
Yeah.

00:20:44.740 --> 00:20:46.310
I really do.

00:20:51.350 --> 00:20:52.340
Then…

00:20:53.280 --> 00:20:54.930
Shall we continue?

00:21:03.130 --> 00:21:06.820
They say a peach holds both sweetness

00:21:07.660 --> 00:21:10.000
And fragility within the same fruit.

00:21:11.240 --> 00:21:12.840
Soft and gentle on the outside,

00:21:13.290 --> 00:21:13.970
Tempting to taste.

00:21:15.200 --> 00:21:16.690
But when you go a little deeper,

00:21:17.380 --> 00:21:18.840
You begin to taste its true flavor.

00:21:23.330 --> 00:21:26.320
Sometimes so sweet it sets your heart racing,

00:21:26.960 --> 00:21:29.350
Sometimes so sharp and bitter it’s almost unbearable.

00:21:30.780 --> 00:21:32.270
Relationships can be the same.

00:21:32.570 --> 00:21:34.190
They begin with the slightest pull,

00:21:34.540 --> 00:21:35.770
Like the scent of fruit drifting through the air.

00:21:38.590 --> 00:21:40.000
But once you truly experience it,

00:21:40.440 --> 00:21:42.540
Someone may become another kind of flavor,

00:21:43.270 --> 00:21:45.040
One you want to remember for the rest of your life.

00:22:36.440 --> 00:22:37.780
Did you need something, Khun Sasom?

00:22:38.030 --> 00:22:39.960
Can I use your room to talk to Thana for a bit?

00:22:40.250 --> 00:22:41.620
I don’t want to disturb Po.

00:22:41.620 --> 00:22:42.440
Sure.

00:22:52.160 --> 00:22:55.220
So? You said you wanted to talk to me,

00:22:55.220 --> 00:22:57.530
But when I called, you hung up.

00:22:57.770 --> 00:22:59.400
What’s going on with you?

00:22:59.690 --> 00:23:00.560
Yeah…

00:23:00.560 --> 00:23:01.370
Sorry, man.

00:23:01.770 --> 00:23:03.180
I had to move to another room to make the call.

00:23:03.470 --> 00:23:04.340
Move to another room?

00:23:04.580 --> 00:23:06.090
Why? What’s the problem?

00:23:06.930 --> 00:23:08.040
It’s just…

00:23:08.490 --> 00:23:10.000
I didn’t want to disturb someone who’s sleeping.

00:23:10.240 --> 00:23:11.650
Sleeping?

00:23:11.650 --> 00:23:12.800
Who?

00:23:14.380 --> 00:23:17.840
Sasom, don’t go quiet on me, or I’m dragging Vic into this.

00:23:18.130 --> 00:23:19.210
Po. Po.

00:23:19.560 --> 00:23:21.030
I didn’t want to disturb Po while he’s sleeping.

00:23:21.280 --> 00:23:22.940
So I moved to another room to talk to you.

00:23:23.230 --> 00:23:24.120
That’s it.

00:23:24.120 --> 00:23:25.610
Shit.

00:23:25.950 --> 00:23:27.200
Don’t tell Vic yet, okay?

00:23:27.750 --> 00:23:29.740
Relax, it’s none of my business. I won’t say anything.

00:23:30.340 --> 00:23:31.380
But damn, I’m shocked.

00:23:31.720 --> 00:23:33.870
I didn’t think Po would end up there with you.

00:23:34.270 --> 00:23:35.510
Weren’t you supposed to be there for work?

00:23:35.950 --> 00:23:36.610
Yeah.

00:23:36.860 --> 00:23:37.610
I thought so too.

00:23:38.690 --> 00:23:40.260
Then how did he get there?

00:23:40.950 --> 00:23:42.220
He flew in to surprise me.

00:23:42.710 --> 00:23:44.060
Probably to thank me

00:23:44.310 --> 00:23:45.530
About that Master Long mess.

00:23:45.770 --> 00:23:46.860
Oh.

00:23:46.860 --> 00:23:48.320
Well, that’s good then.

00:23:48.320 --> 00:23:50.230
So why are you calling me about it?

00:23:52.300 --> 00:23:53.590
It’s just…

00:23:55.520 --> 00:23:57.090
I don’t want to film with Po anymore.

00:23:58.230 --> 00:24:00.270
What? What did you just say?

00:24:01.060 --> 00:24:03.520
I said I don’t want to film with Po anymore.

00:24:04.110 --> 00:24:05.650
Hey, why? What happened?

00:24:05.900 --> 00:24:07.420
I mean, you…

00:24:08.160 --> 00:24:10.710
Yeah, I know.

00:24:11.060 --> 00:24:12.870
I know what you’re going to say.

00:24:13.560 --> 00:24:14.970
I still have feelings for him.

00:24:15.810 --> 00:24:17.790
But I don’t want to film with him anymore.

00:24:18.770 --> 00:24:21.700
Damn, you’re not usually like this.

00:24:22.390 --> 00:24:24.200
Yeah, I know.

00:24:24.790 --> 00:24:26.280
I just…

00:24:26.280 --> 00:24:27.360
Shit.

00:24:27.650 --> 00:24:28.910
That’s enough.

00:24:29.260 --> 00:24:30.500
Don’t tell me.

00:24:30.740 --> 00:24:32.470
The one you should be saying all this to is—

00:24:32.470 --> 00:24:33.220
Over there.

00:24:33.220 --> 00:24:34.030
Po.

00:24:34.480 --> 00:24:35.550
But…

00:24:35.890 --> 00:24:37.760
What now?

00:24:40.720 --> 00:24:41.930
I’m scared.

00:24:41.930 --> 00:24:43.670
Scared?

00:24:45.650 --> 00:24:46.440
I’m scared.

00:24:47.920 --> 00:24:49.550
I’m scared that Po might just…

00:24:50.340 --> 00:24:51.310
Just…

00:24:51.750 --> 00:24:52.420
Just what?

00:24:53.950 --> 00:24:55.500
That he only wants to film with me.

00:25:00.000 --> 00:25:01.090
I mean…

00:25:01.490 --> 00:25:04.670
I want you to start taking filming more seriously.

00:25:06.990 --> 00:25:08.830
Are you jealous of me?

00:25:09.920 --> 00:25:11.200
Why would you be jealous of me?

00:25:11.640 --> 00:25:12.660
We’re going to have to film anyway.

00:25:13.790 --> 00:25:15.940
And people are going to see more of me soon.

00:25:16.680 --> 00:25:18.380
So…

00:25:20.300 --> 00:25:23.400
If you help me film with you,

00:25:27.050 --> 00:25:28.770
Just that,

00:25:31.920 --> 00:25:33.850
Would already help me a lot.

00:27:15.410 --> 00:27:17.470
Maybe I’ve been leaning on him too much.

00:27:20.000 --> 00:27:22.020
Maybe being apart for a while

00:27:25.130 --> 00:27:27.270
Gives me the space to sit with myself like this.

00:27:28.600 --> 00:27:29.650
Maybe that’s not such a bad thing.

00:27:34.880 --> 00:27:37.160
Maybe I need time to reflect.

00:27:38.340 --> 00:27:39.780
Stop overthinking, Po.

00:28:43.770 --> 00:28:45.770
I haven’t seen his face in almost a week.

00:28:48.830 --> 00:28:50.590
Ever since we got back from Singapore,

00:28:50.830 --> 00:28:52.190
He’s been staying in Kanchanaburi,

00:28:52.640 --> 00:28:54.640
Shooting a new series that just started production.

00:29:10.480 --> 00:29:12.570
Are you secretly snapping photos of me?

00:29:14.890 --> 00:29:16.570
Secretly? Of course not.

00:29:16.570 --> 00:29:18.090
I’m snapping them right in front of you.

00:29:18.090 --> 00:29:19.100
You…

00:29:19.100 --> 00:29:21.300
With the light this bright, do you think I’ll look okay?

00:29:22.090 --> 00:29:23.150
You’ll look fine.

00:29:23.150 --> 00:29:24.260
Look.

00:29:25.150 --> 00:29:27.150
I look more sleepy than anything.

